  "instructions": [
    "Heat oil in a wok or large skillet over medium-high heat.",
    "Add garlic and ginger; sauté until fragrant, about 30 seconds.",
    "Add mung bean sprouts and cook for about 2 minutes, stirring occasionally to prevent sticking.",
    "Pour in soy sauce, rice vinegar, sesame oil, five spice powder, and pepper flakes. Stir well to combine ingredients evenly.",
    "Let the mixture simmer until slightly thickened, about 3-5 minutes. If desired, stir in cooked white rice as a garnish.",
    "Sprinkle with toasted sesame seeds before serving."
